  "text": "The xDS v3 transport protocol in Envoy is implemented across two architecture layers:\n\n1. **Legacy Implementation (still maintained):**\n   - `GrpcSubscriptionImpl` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.{h,cc}): The subscription adapter that wraps a GrpcMux and bridges subscription callbacks to the mux operations.\n   - `GrpcMuxImpl` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.{h,cc}): Manages xDS subscriptions using State-of-the-World (SotW) protocol with DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse messages.\n   - `NewGrpcMuxImpl` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.{h,cc}): Manages xDS subscriptions using Delta protocol with DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse messages.\n\n2. **Unified XdsMux Template Implementation (migration target):**\n   - `GrpcMuxImpl<S, F, RQ, RS>` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.{h,cc}): A template-based generic mux that accepts subscription state types (S), state factories (F), request types (RQ), and response types (RS). This unified template handles both SotW and Delta protocols through specialization.\n   - Concrete specializations:\n     - `GrpcMuxSotw`: Specializes the template with `SotwSubscriptionState`, `SotwSubscriptionStateFactory`, `DiscoveryRequest`, and `DiscoveryResponse`\n     - `GrpcMuxDelta`: Specializes the template with `DeltaSubscriptionState`, `DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory`, `DeltaDiscoveryRequest`, and `DeltaDiscoveryResponse`\n   - Supporting state implementations:\n     - `BaseSubscriptionState<RS, RQ>` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/subscription_state.h): Abstract base for subscription protocol state tracking\n     - `SotwSubscriptionState` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.{h,cc}): State-of-the-World implementation with version tracking and full resource list updates\n     - `DeltaSubscriptionState` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.{h,cc}): Delta implementation with per-resource versioning and incremental updates\n     - `SubscriptionStateFactory<T>` template (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/subscription_state.h): Abstract factory for creating subscription states\n     - `SotwSubscriptionStateFactory` and `DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory` (in respective .h files): Concrete factories\n\n3. **Factory Selection Logic:**\n   - `GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_factory.{h,cc}): Selects between legacy `GrpcMuxImpl` and unified `GrpcMuxSotw` based on the `envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux` runtime flag. Creates `GrpcSubscriptionImpl` wrapping the selected mux.\n   - `DeltaGrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory` (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_factory.{h,cc}): Selects between legacy `NewGrpcMuxImpl` and unified `GrpcMuxDelta` based on the unified_mux feature flag.\n   - Both factories create `GrpcSubscriptionImpl` to provide a uniform subscription interface.\n\nThe architecture supports a migration from the dual-mux design (GrpcMuxImpl and NewGrpcMuxImpl) to a unified template-based mux (XdsMux::GrpcMuxImpl with specializations) controlled by feature flags for safe rollout."
}

